wiki.text:
The term 'quantitative' refers to a type of information based in quantities or
else quantifiable data (objective properties) —as opposed to 'qualitative'
information which deals with apparent (subjective properties). It may also refer
to mass, time, or productivity. *Quantitative research, scientific investigation
of quantitative properties *Quantitative verse, a metrical system in poetry
*Statistics, also known as quantitative analysis *Numerical data, also known as
quantitative data
